name: Private Pondok
address: H3WR+Q72, Sangketan, Penebel, Tabanan Regency, Bali 82152, Indonesia
review 1:
Hello... I want to share my holiday experience in this family compound located in remote village in Penebel, Bali. The building where I stay is separate from the main building where the owner lives with his family and a very cute dog.  The building has two rooms, with a beautiful traditional Balinese design.  Apart from the incredible views of the mountains and rice fields, there are many other places to visit around the village such as several waterfalls and natural hot springs. The owner also took us to his family's rice fields, went fishing, swimming in the small river, and attended a traditional ceremony at the temple in traditional Balinese costumes.  We are provided with fresh organic food from their own garden.  I also tried their very good honey from their own farm.  All of that at a very affordable price. There's no public transportation but they provide cars and motorbikes to rent with the reasonable price.
For those of you who are bored with the hustle and bustle of Bali and want to travel in a quiet place, I highly recommend this place. I would love to come back here again one day.
